\begin{align*}
\tan \theta &= \frac{1 - \tan \alpha}{1 + \tan \alpha} \\
&= \frac{1 - \frac{\sin \alpha}{\cos \alpha}}{1 + \frac{\sin \alpha}{\cos \alpha}} \\
&= \frac{\cos \alpha - \sin \alpha}{\cos \alpha + \sin \alpha} \\
&= \frac{1 - \sin \alpha}{1 + \sin \alpha} \\
&= \frac{1 - \frac{1 - \cos 2 \alpha}{2}}{1 + \frac{1 - \cos 2 \alpha}{2}} \\
&= \frac{\cos 2 \alpha + 1}{\cos 2 \alpha - 1} \\
&= \frac{2 \cos^2 \alpha}{2 \cos^2 \alpha - 2} \\
&= \frac{2 \cos^2 \alpha - 2 + 2}{2 \cos^2 \alpha - 2} \\
&= \boxed{1}.
\end{align*}The answer is 1

